args: It's gotta be the boss of all them fiends\naround here.
Good thing I like a challenge!
That sigh was pretty intense, even for you.
Well. The boor speaks. And just whose\nfault do you think it is I'm IN this state?
Psst! Do you remember bumping into him\nwhen you dodged that attack a while back?
Wait, what? Oh man, I'm real sorry 'bout\nthat. It's just that when I start fightin' I—
How is my hair? Is there dirt on my face?\nMy sanity hangs by a gossamer thread!
Someone bring me a shiny object!\nI'LL TAKE ANYTHING I CAN GET!
I really don't think this is the time for that\nparticular conversation, people!
The fiend is bracing to attack!
I can't be here right now. I have to get\nback to the castle and retrieve one of my\nspare mirro—
M-my face... This filthy fiend cut my FACE!
A smudge of dirt or dust and I might\nhave just killed you...but a CUT?!
Prepare to suffer unimaginable pain, fiend!
I had no idea the guy was that strong.\n...I shoulda smashed his mirror ages ago.
That was amazin'! It's completely changed\nthe way I see y—
No one cares about any of that!\nNOW BRING ME A MIRROR!
I have a CUT on my FACE!
You're going to be all right. Here, have a\nlook for yourself in this glass.
A shallow nick like that will heal in no\ntime, with nary a scar left behind.
Oh, whew... This face is all I have left to\nremind me of Mother. If I—
This...this is unthinkable. My sweat-slick\nhair, my grit-stained cheek...
I just fought a grueling battle,\nand I am GLOWING!
Thank you, Ranzal! This is an incredible\ndiscovery, and it never would have\nhappened if you hadn't broken my mirror!
Uh...sure? Don't really get it, but hey.\nWhat're friends for, yeah?
